'''Islam Yahyayevich Timurziev''' ({{lang-ru|Ислам Яхьяевич Тимурзиев}}; 9 January 1983 – 31 August 2015) was an [[Ingush people|Ingush]]  amateur boxer from Russia best known for winning the European superheavyweight title in 2006.

==Career==
Born in [[Nazran]], [[Ingushetia]], Timurziev started boxing in 1996. He is a skilled offensive fighter with impressive power in both hands but has defensive weaknesses. He won the U-17 European Championship in 1999, and the Junior European Championships in 2001.

He added the military world title in 2003, and won the 2004 Russian national title, but only after he helped his national team winning the [[Boxing World Cup|Nations World Cup]] by beating Cuban [[Odlanier Solis]] (Olympic Champion at 201&nbsp;lbs) on points. Later that year he was out with cancer, his compatriot [[Roman Romanchuk (boxer)|Roman Romanchuk]] participated in the world championships.

In 2006, Timurziev made a comeback claiming the [[2006 European Amateur Boxing Championships|European title]] with wins over [[Roberto Cammarelle]], [[Kubrat Pulev]] and [[Robert Helenius]].
At the [[Boxing World Cup|World Cup]] in Baku, Timurziev was pulled out by his corner in a rematch by his nemesis Odlanier Solis. This also granted Cuba a 6-5 win of the cup.

Timurziev was in bad form early on in 2007, losing in the Russian championships against the unsung [[Denis Sergeev]] (19:22).

But at the [[2007 World Amateur Boxing Championships]] in Chicago he reached the semi-finals among others with several first round wins and a points victory over American [[Michael Hunter (American boxer)|Michael Hunter]]. He was unable to advance further, suffering from acute appendicitis, thus granting [[Roberto Cammarelle]] a win on walkover, and earning the bronze medal.

Timurziev was regarded as the favorite at the 2008 Beijing Olympics in his weightclass as the Cubans were lacking a star in this class after Solis had defected. He was defeated though by Great Britain's [[David Price (boxer)|David Price]] through a knockout in the second round.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2008/aug/13/olympicsboxing.olympics2008|title=Olympics: David Price knocks out European champion Islam Timurziev|last=Mitchell|first=Kevin|date=13 August 2008|work=[[The Guardian]]|accessdate=3 November 2014}}</ref>

He died in hospital of [[sepsis]] on 31 August 2015, following a long illness.<ref>[http://sport.segodnya.ua/boxing/byvshiy-bokser-olimpiyskoy-sbornoy-rossii-skonchalsya-v-vozraste-32-let-645450.html Бывший боксер олимпийской сборной России скончался в возрасте 32 лет]</ref>

